  <p>About:</p>
  
  <p id="bio"><img src="Portrait.jpg" id="thumbnail"> Lauren Saine is a lawyer who writes on tech policy in San Francisco.  She has more than ten years of experience in public policy analysis, most recently as legal and policy advisor at the California Public Utilities Commission and previously as legislative analyst for the Colorado Legislature's Joint Budget Committee.  She also served as a management consultant with the Mountain States Employers Council. Lauren holds a JD with honors from the University of Denver College of Law and a Certificate in Strategic Management from the Harvard Kennedy School's Executive Education Program.  She is a novice coder and an active member of the Startup Policy Lab, Women Who Code, and SFHTML5 study groups.</p>

